ring startup task execution using `BaseItem.syncShareCache` data, ensuring cached share state is populated in Redux before CommandService and KeymapService initialization.|\n\n</details>\n\n<!-- walkthrough_end -->\n\n\n<!-- pre_merge_checks_walkthrough_start -->\n\n<details>\n<summary>🚥 Pre-merge checks | ✅ 6</summary>\n\n<details>\n<summary>✅ Passed checks (6 passed)</summary>\n\n|               Check name              | Status   | Explanation                                                                                                                                                                                                         |\n| :-----------------------------------: | :------- | :------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------ |\n|              Title check              | ✅ Passed | The title accurately describes the primary fix: showing correct notebook context menu options when the server is offline by ensuring share state is properly initialized.                                           |\n|           Description check           | ✅ Passed | The description clearly explains the problem, root cause, solution, and test plan, all directly related to the changeset.                                                                                           |\n|          Linked Issues check          | ✅ Passed | The PR successfully implements the requirements from issue `#12994`: it ensures the share owner sees 'Share notebook...' instead of 'Leave notebook...' when the server is offline by seeding share state from cache. |\n|       Out of Scope Changes check      | ✅ Passed | All changes are directly scoped to seeding share service state from cache during startup; no unrelated modifications to sync or sharing logic are present.                                                          |\n|    